The paper deals with the problem of efficient distributed spectrum sharing, which is a topic of interest in several sub-fields of computer science. However, the focus on spatial aspects of spectrum sharing suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of game theory to model the problem further supports this hypothesis, as both cs.IT and cs.NI have a strong tradition of using game theory in their research. The paper may also be relevant to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories, as these fields also deal with distributed decision-making problems. Finally, the use of learning algorithms and convergence analysis suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category.
